So, 
# known universe = 13.7 billion light years. 
# Known planets harbouring intelligent life = 1 (earth). 
# Total nuclear megatonnage on planet earth = 5,000
# Megatonnage required to destroy all life on Earth = 100 Megatons.
# Number of times we can destroy the only planet within 13.7 billion light years which harbours intelligent life: 50.

And we can do it in an afternoon. Toss in Murphy's Law and prepare for grandest folly.
